    "narrative": "The projected lineup for Ghost Ride the WHIP leans heavily into favorable matchups against higher-ERA arms, with **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Corbin Carroll** (71.33) serving as our offensive pillars today. **Mickey Moniak** is positioned for a breakout game against Roki Sasaki; while the matchup against a high-velo arm is typically daunting, the +14% park factor and the +14% boost from a dynamic platoon advantage elevate him into elite territory. Similarly, **Corbin Carroll** remains a must-start despite facing Kevin Gausman. Though the SP skill adjustment is negative, **Corbin Carroll**\u2019s elite xwOBA (0.372) and the efficiency of his spot in the two-hole make him the highest-floor asset in our outfield. **Max Muncy** (71.26) also provides significant value, capitalizing on a weak matchup against Noah Schultz, where the +19% SP skill advantage effectively negates the downgrade of batting seventh.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Alex Freeland**, whose 53.79 score fell just short of the active roster. While **Alex Freeland** benefits from a strong park factor against Michael Lorenzen, the optimizer favored the higher lineup seniority of **James Wood** (66.69) and the specific stolen base environment provided by **Brice Turang**. **James Wood**\u2019s leadoff status provides a critical +10% order boost, and the team's commitment to prioritizing SB threats keeps **Brice Turang** locked in\u2014even with a neutral matchup\u2014because his ability to exploit Eury P\u00e9rez\u2019s slow delivery remains a strategic imperative. We are also monitoring a 34% rain risk for **Seiya Suzuki**; while his 64.64 score remains robust, any precipitation-related delays could impact his efficiency, making him a potential late-swap candidate if the weather worsens. \n\nWe continue to leave high-upside options like **Vinnie Pasquantino** (51.31) and **Josh Naylor** (51.23) on the bench. In both cases, the optimizer prioritized the platoon stability of our active starters over their raw projection, particularly as **Vinnie Pasquantino** faces a difficult dynamic platoon disadvantage against Ryan Weathers. With **Dalton Rushing**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, **Trevor Story**, **Austin Riley**, **Jose Caballero**, and **Kyle Karros** rounding out the squad, we are leaning into the high-variance, high-reward matchups presented by today\u2019s slate to maintain our edge in the 5x5 standings.",
